Santander’s Andre Berenguer to Head Brazil Investment Bank

-- B y   G a b r i e l l e   C o p p o l a
-- 
2011-03-01T15:44:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/santander-s-andre-berenguer-to-head-brazil-investment-bank.html
Banco Santander Brasil SA, the
Brazilian unit of  Spain ’s biggest bank, named Andre Berenguer to
run corporate and investment banking, according to the bank’s
press department in Sao Paulo.  Berenguer, 43, is the brother of Jose Berenguer, senior
vice-president responsible for asset management and private
banking at Santander. Andre Berenguer will replace Luiz Reis,
who left at the beginning of the year, the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gabrielle Coppola in Sao Paulo at 
 gcoppola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
 papadopoulous@bloomberg.net  